Looking at the code, I can see that the problem is in the `format(Date date, StringBuffer buf)` method:

```java
public StringBuffer format(Date date, StringBuffer buf) {
    Calendar c = new GregorianCalendar(mTimeZone);
    c.setTime(date);
    return applyRules(c, buf);
}
```

And also in the `format(Date date)` method:
```java
public String format(Date date) {
    Calendar c = new GregorianCalendar(mTimeZone);
    c.setTime(date);
    return applyRules(c, new StringBuffer(mMaxLengthEstimate)).toString();
}
```

These methods should respect the locale when creating the calendar. Let me fix both methods:

